 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uimmlazen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Immlazen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#333333>(10/14/02 7:05:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Planar Renewal - level 64 pet heal - 1250 hp / 400 mana</span><hr size=1> The heal is a decent one but I think it should be for 250-300 Mana.  Nothing more.  Look at the mana cost for Beastlords and Necros.  The beastlord cost the same amount in mana but heals for twice as much.  The Necro can heal there pets 3 times for the same mana it takes ours for one heal.  It is no reason why ours should be behind a Necros.  Also, going back to the old heals in Original EQ. Necros got there pet heals the same time and for the same amount of mana as Magicians.  Why is there a disparity now?  What has changed?<br>
<br>
Verant if you are reading these boards: I know you deal in computations, so my question is how do you get to these numbers compared to other Pet classes?  Also, if Maicians are the main pet class with Pets being there main attributes, why are we not being looked at first with the best heals and buffs for our pets?<br>
<br>
<br>
Immlazen<br>
