<br>
Magicians pets have better damage mitigation and avoidance than other pets, thus they tank better, and take less damage overall.<br>
<br>
Necromancer pets don't tank well, and take large amounts of damage, thus need more healing.<br>
<br>
Beastlords have a high numbers heal to quickly revive their pet, but also has no recast so can be chained.  However, as a Hybrid, they have a smaller mana pool.<br>
<br>
I don't see anything wrong with Necromancers having a &quot;better&quot; (read: more efficient) heal than we do, or with beastlords having a &quot;bigger&quot; heal than we do.  I do however think that the ratio on our heal needs to be reviewed.<br>
<br>
If I can summon a pet with 4k HP for 400 mana, a 1K heal for 200-250 mana shouldn't be out of the question.<br>
<br>
Not everyone has the level 60 pet heal.  I wonder how obtainable this new heal spell will be.... <p><FONT SIZE="3" COLOR=#FFFFFF FACE="Comic Sans MS, Sans-Serif, Courier New, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">
