Both Bl warder and Spectre pet are as good tanks as any mage pet.<br>
Both Warder and Spectre have more Hp than all mage pets except earth, and both of them avoid hits better than Earthpet.<br>
<br>
People also forgeting something, both necros and BLs have ways of making pet take less dmg, both have slow, and even if necros are undead only they have always Fearkite.<br>
<br>
Mages should have the best pet heals really, I can accept that BLs have better since they are a priest class, but I see no reason why necros should been better, and why on earth is the mana ratio so insane for necro heal, they have afterall the best manaregen of all classes.<br>
<br>
Mage epic is ofcourse ahead rest of the pets then it come to tanking, but there is a good chance our PoP pets will be better than Epic and it is also probaly true that Necro, BL and mage pets will be about equal at L65. <br>
And really, why would a BL even consider tanking and take dmg? With a 2k heal, good manaregen and a 65% slow he can kill alot of really hard stuff tons more effective than a mage just playing pet cleric. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzebanar01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zebanar01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 279<br> <font color=#333333>(10/16/02 2:09:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hmm..</span><hr size=1> Don't forget, that magicians DO have summon phantom plate, and it indeed does make a difference to their AC. <br>
<br>
